HEADWORD: light-sensitive
<hw>light-sensitive</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Affected by
light; <as>as, the <ex>light-sensitive</ex> pigments in the
retina</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> photosensitive.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <specif>Hence:</specif> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>Decomposing under the influence of light; unstable when exposed to
light; -- of chemical compounds.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Light-ship</ent>⟦br⟧
